The '''FD number''', or '''Fire/Disable number''', was a number used to measure the effectiveness of artillery pieces. It was a simple ratio, calculated by dividing the time during which the artillery tube fired by the time required for it to cool down and recharge. Weapons with higher FD numbers could fire more frequently. More powerful weapons tended to have lower FD numbers. First used in the [[Atrisi system|Atrisian system]], it was later used by the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Service]], [[Atgar SpaceDefense Corporation/Legends|Atgar SpaceDefense Corporation]], and [[CoMar Combat Systems/Legends|CoMar Combat Systems]] to categorize artillery units.<ref name="IS">''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''</ref>

